Large language models (LLMs) are advanced artificial intelligence systems trained on vast amounts of text data to understand and generate human-like language. Built using deep learning techniques, particularly transformer architectures, they can process and produce text across multiple languages, answer questions, write stories, code, and engage in conversations. Their ability to capture context and patterns from massive datasets enables them to perform tasks like translation, summarization, and creative writing. LLMs are widely applied in fields such as customer service, education, research, and content creation, revolutionizing how humans interact with and leverage language-based technologies.
